<TITLE> School timings changed, except Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 19 (bdnews24.com)The government has rescheduled timings for secondary level schools and madrasas throughout the country, except for the capital, an education ministry order said Sunday. All schools, which teach up to higher secondary level, will come under the new timings, deputy secretary for education Moijuddin Ahmed told bdnews24com. According to the new schedule, schools with one shift will start at 10am and continue for six hours. At present, most schools begin classes start at 8am. For double-shift schools, classes will start at 8am and two consecutive shifts will run for at least five hours each, said the order. . School authorities will fix the timetables according to their convenience. Schools in the Dhaka city area, which currently start at 7am, will not come under the new schedule. bdne
